reholders we believe that by ensuring the safety and longterm health of our employees are not compromised and that by being a good neighbor in the communities in which we live and work value will be maximized we will run the business in a sustainable way to ensure we maintain our “license to operate” ie support of employees communities regulators elected officials customers suppliers our current strategy is to build on our strong us domestic position to develop our export sales and explore international production opportunities our values cloud peak energy’s values are the underlying principles that guide the way we do business we will hold each other accountable to not deviate from these values in all our business dealings safety – the safety of everyone involved in our business will never be compromised caring – we care about the impact of our actions on people and the environment both inside and outside the company honesty – we are honest and transparent in all interactions with each other and those outside the company courage – we will be courageous in all our dealings and will hold ourselves accountable for our actions and not avoid difficult issues respect – we will show respect to all those involved in every interaction and work to engage all our employees in the business back to tophome about us issues and where we stand environmental programs health and safety program sustainable development program health safety and environmental policy management colin marshall heath hill bryan pechersky gary rivenes amy clemetson bruce jones todd myers operations antelope mine cordero rojo mine spring creek mine news media press releases publications investor relations analyst coverage annual reports corporate governance email alerts events calendar frequently asked questions presentations press releases announcements business development corporate earnings operations request for information sec filings cloud peak energy inc cloud peak energy resources llc stock informat